race.comment: STELLAR MOFEED (6) resumes. She doesn't win out of turn but was racing in good form last preparation, placing in her past four starts before the break in comparatively strong races. She goes very well fresh with 2 wins and should go well here. ESCARPA (4) is flying this time in. She tested a very progressive horse in Tennessee Bound two back and was good again last time in a similar race. She'll be hard to hold out. ATTACHMENTS (1) is a progressive sort off a smart win at Kilmore when scoring by 2.25 lengths. She has plenty of upside at just her sixth start and can go on with it now. BRILLIANT HORIZON (9) is another with upside who has been solid in two runs back. She gets Willo on from the inside gate now and can win. PATH TO PROFIT (10) got her maiden out of the way last time and has claims.
